<div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yhd1665702836348.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yhd1665702836348.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yhd1665702836348\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Print\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Print data from the current form.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yhd1665702836348__section_w138ab1b7b1_w139ab1b7_w140ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yhd1665702836348__section_w141ab1b7b3_w142ab1b7_w143ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d992079e60\">\n                       \n Fields\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yhd1665702836348__li_d4493e1_d4494e1_d4495e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lsn1665702836417.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsn1665702836417.html\" title=\"Name of the print job model to use. The default name is PRINTER.\">Print Job Model</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yhd1665702836348__li_d4496e1_d4497e1_d4498e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"owv1665702836486.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/owv1665702836486.html\" title=\"Specify the data to print.\">Print Mode</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yhd1665702836348__section_w144ab1b7b5_w145ab1b7_w146ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d992079e89\">\n                       \n How to\n </h2>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yhd1665702836348__li_d4499e1_d4500e1_d4501e1\">Select the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Mode</span> you want.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yhd1665702836348__li_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1\">To choose a different print job model, clear the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Job Model</span> field or enter a retrieve profile, and\n               click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">&gt;&gt;</span>. In the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Browse Print Job\n                  Model</span> form, select the model you want to use and click\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span>. <p class=\"p\" id=\"yhd1665702836348__p_d9827e1_d9828e1_d9829e1\">If you want to define\n                  a new print job model, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">New</span>. See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nbh1665702675570.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nbh1665702675570.html\" title=\"You must define a print job model before you can print data from Form components.\">Define a Print Job Model</a>. </p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yhd1665702836348__li_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span> to print.\n </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534097\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534097\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Print Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Print Print data from the current form. Fields Print Job Model Print Mode How to Select the Print Mode you want. To choose a different print job model, clear the Print Job Model field or enter a retrieve profile, and click >> . In the Browse Print Job Model form, select the model you want to use and click OK . If you want to define a new print job model, click New . See Define a Print Job Model . Click OK to print. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}